The quantity described is the **Lorentz force**.  

In Lagrangian mechanics, the Lorentz force arises from a potential \( U = q(\phi - \mathbf{v} \cdot \mathbf{A}) \), and the Euler-Lagrange equations yield \( \mathbf{F} = q(-\nabla \phi - \frac{d\mathbf{A}}{dt} + \nabla(\mathbf{v} \cdot \mathbf{A})) \), which simplifies to the familiar Lorentz force law.  

\boxed{\text{Lorentz force}}
